			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~Gavagai80">Gavagai80</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~Gavagai80">( 1275204 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64447754"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64447754"><p>China has a long-declared no first strike policy, and maintains a relatively small nuclear arsenal because of it. They promise not to use nuclear weapons unless you use them on them first. That doesn't take an AI, it's a pretty simple IF-THEN.</p><p>If the USA believes China's no first strike policy, then calling for a no AI policy is pointless. If the USA doesn't believe China's no first strike policy, then calling for a no AI policy is senseless. Which goes to show what this is all about: a transparent propagand<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

